Step 1: run "make" to make mdb or mdb_nvm version
Step 2: run make to make libleveldb in directory ./leveldb
Step 3: In this directory, run g++ -I ./leveldb/include -c testutil.cc
Step 4: In this directoru, run g++ -I ./leveldb/include -c db_bench_mdb.cc
Step 5: g++ -pthread db_bench_mdb.o testutil.o -L ./.. -L ./leveldb -static -lmdb -lleveldb

Note: There is no particular reason for the libraries to be linked statically other than convenience.
Make sure that the otimization level and debugging is set properly in makefile(s) before running make on mdb and leveldb

List of sub-benchmarks and description is provided in db_bench_mdb.cc. To run a subset of them:
./a.out --benchmarks="fillrandsync,writewdsdsd"


